notes: mortality = "Z. marina mortality was assessed by deploying a weight of 26 g to the shoots. Z. marina shoots usually show signs of mortality by a softening in the transi- tion region between the above and below-ground parts (Greve et al., 2003). Only plants able to resist the weight were considered as a survivor"
driver notes: 120 was minimum light; used study 97 Fe because same source sediments and authors; missing salinity and grain size can probably be imputed using study 97 data
